Prospera OS
Documentation Style Guide v1.2

File: kernel/documentation-style-guide-v1.2
Status: Stable
Owner: Prospera Architecture Group
Category: Kernel Specification

Purpose
This document defines the formatting, structural, linguistic, and metadata standards for all Prospera OS documents.
All specifications, contracts, protocols, engines, modules, maps, and integration files must comply with this guide.
Non-compliant documents must be corrected by Governance.

Language Rules
2.1 All documents must be written in technical English.
2.2 No mixed-language content is permitted.
2.3 Terms must remain consistent across the entire repository.
2.4 Natural-language explanations must remain concise and deterministic.

Metadata Block Rules
3.1 Each file must begin with the following header:

Prospera OS
<Document Title> vX.Y

File: <path/to/file>
Status: <Draft | Stable | Deprecated>
Owner: <Team or Group>
Category: <Kernel | Governance | System | Engine | Module | Contract | Protocol | Map>

3.2 Metadata must contain no additional fields.
3.3 Version numbers must follow Kernel-defined versioning rules.
3.4 File paths must match repository structure exactly.

Section Structure Rules
4.1 All documents must follow numbered sections.
4.2 Section numbers must not skip or repeat.
4.3 Each top-level section must begin with a single line break before content.
4.4 Subsections must follow n.n formatting.
4.5 Section titles must not include symbols, Markdown accents, or bolding.

Content Formatting Rules
5.1 All paragraphs must be separated by exactly one blank line.
5.2 Excessive line breaks must be removed.
5.3 Lists must use simple numeric or hyphen formats without Markdown symbols.
5.4 No inline styles, emphasis markers, or Markdown formatting is allowed.
5.5 All content must follow deterministic ordering.

File Naming and Location Rules
6.1 Filenames must follow the structure:

<name>-<type>-vX.Y.md

6.2 All documents must reside in the correct layer directory.
6.3 Deprecated files must be placed under /deprecated.
6.4 No duplicate filenames are allowed.
6.5 File paths must match the metadata File field exactly.

Cross-Layer Boundary Rules
7.1 Documents must reference only their own layer and approved dependency layers.
7.2 System documents cannot reference Engines or Modules.
7.3 Engine documents cannot reference Modules or Platforms.
7.4 Module documents cannot reference Systems or Engines.
7.5 Boundary violations must be removed immediately.

Terminology Rules
8.1 All terminology must align with Kernel version.
8.2 Terms must remain consistent across Systems, Engines, and Modules.
8.3 Deprecated terms must not appear in any v1.2 document.
8.4 Terminology drift is prohibited.

Version Alignment Rules
9.1 All documents must declare version alignment to Kernel v1.2.
9.2 Cross-version documents must be updated or removed.
9.3 Version mismatches must be blocked by Governance.
9.4 System, Engine, and Module must increment versions in sync with Kernel.

File Ending Rules
10.1 All documents must end with the following standard block:

────────────────────────────────────────
End of Document
────────────────────────────────────────

10.2 No extra content may appear after the End of Document block.
10.3 A single blank line is required before and after the End of Document block.

Enforcement Rules
11.1 Governance must validate all documents before acceptance.
11.2 Non-compliant documents must be automatically migrated.
11.3 New documents must enforce v1.2 standard by default.
11.4 Violations must halt document acceptance until corrected.
11.5 This guide overrides all earlier style definitions.

File Location
kernel/documentation-style-guide-v1.2

────────────────────────────────────────
End of Document
────────────────────────────────────────
